parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seatbelt to remain loose, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The seatbelts do not retract
the seatbelts are loose while worn
the seatbelts fail to lock in place during sudden stops or crashes
the seatbelts get caught in the retractor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil spots under the vehicle
oil smell inside the vehicle
low oil level warning
engine noise or knocking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose electrical power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the battery warning light comes on
the electrical system malfunctions
the vehicle's accessories (e.g.
radio
lights) fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can increase the risk of accidents, especially on slippery or uneven roads.
symptoms: The ABS warning light comes on
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes make unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Short Circuit in Driver's Seat Motor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short circuit in the driver's seat motor can cause a fire, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke emission from the driver's seat area
burning smell
and potentially a visible fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunction in the fuel cell can cause a meltdown, leading to a potential fire hazard, and potentially causing damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: Unidentified switch failure
fuel cell meltdown
and potentially a fire or smoke emission.
